message: To succeed, first combine a 'natural, soft' ingredient with an 'artificial, soft' ingredient; this reliably creates an item with value 30. Immediately apply the 'frame' tool to this item, which consistently increases its value to 50. Avoid combining more than two ingredients, as adding a third ingredient almost always results in an 'overcomplicated' item with a negative value. The 'scissors' tool can sometimes mitigate 'overcomplicated' items but often ruins good framed items, so use it sparingly on high-value items. 'Ruined frame' items are generally dead ends.
